HEADWORD: Rompu
<hw>Rom"pu</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>rompu</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>rompre</ets> to breeak, L. <ets>rumpere</ets>. See
<er>Rupture</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Broken, as an ordinary;
cut off, or broken at the top, as a chevron, a bend, or the
like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

